{"reasoning":"The deadlock comes from inconsistent lock ordering: one transfer locks A then B, while the other locks B then A. To make deadlock impossible under any interleaving, both transfers must acquire locks in the same global order. The simplest fix is to make the B→A transfer also lock A first, then B. This preserves correctness and eliminates circular wait. I kept the step-based simulation intact and only changed the locking order in the second transfer.",
